---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Search from '../components/Search.svelte';
import TryIt from '../components/TryIt.svelte';
---

<Base
  title="Committee Translation AI"
  description="Scholarly AI-powered reference for Arabic and Persian sacred texts. Browse parallel translations by Shoghi Effendi across 11 works and 2,500+ passages."
>
  <script slot="head" type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@graph": [
      {
        "@type": "WebSite",
        "name": "CTAI — Committee Translation AI",
        "url": "https://ctai.info/",
        "description": "Scholarly AI-powered reference for Arabic and Persian sacred texts"
      },
      {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "CTAI",
        "url": "https://ctai.info/"
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <!-- ===== HERO ===== -->
  <section class="relative pt-24 pb-20 md:pt-32 md:pb-28">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <!-- Left: headline + quote -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-3">
        <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-gold-500 mb-6 animate-fade-in">Committee Translation AI</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-light text-gold-50 tracking-tight leading-[1.1] mb-10 animate-fade-up">
          The best translations<br />come from a committee.
        </h1>

        <blockquote class="relative pl-6 border-l border-gold-500/40 mb-4 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.15s">
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed italic font-light">
            &ldquo;Whenever it is possible a committee must be organized for the
            translation of the Tablets. Wise souls who have mastered and studied
            perfectly the Persian, Arabic, and other foreign languages&hellip;
            must commence translating Tablets and books containing the proofs
            of this Revelation.&rdquo;
          </p>
        </blockquote>
        <p class="text-xs text-ink-500 font-mono tracking-wide mb-10 pl-6 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.25s">
          &mdash; 'Abdu'l-Bah&aacute;, <em class="not-italic text-ink-400">Tablets of the Divine Plan</em>
        </p>

        <p class="text-ink-400 max-w-xl leading-relaxed animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.35s">
          There's a reason for that. Translation of sacred text isn't a solo sport.
          Every word carries layers &mdash; theological, literary, historical, cultural &mdash;
          and no single mind can hold them all at once.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: Try CTAI -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 lg:sticky lg:top-24 animate-fade-up" style="animation-delay: 0.4s">
        <TryIt client:visible />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== DIVIDER ===== -->
  <div class="flex items-center gap-4 my-4">
    <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-ink-700 to-transparent"></div>
    <span class="font-arabic text-gold-500/30 text-2xl select-none" aria-hidden="true">&#1757;</span>
    <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-ink-700 to-transparent"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== SHOGHI EFFENDI'S STANDARD ===== -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-20">
    <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-ink-500 mb-4">The standard</p>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-10">
      Then Shoghi Effendi raised the bar.
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-ink-300 leading-[1.8]">
      <p>
        For over thirty years, the Guardian of the Bah&aacute;'&iacute; Faith translated
        Bah&aacute;'u'll&aacute;h's Arabic and Persian into some of the most architecturally
        coherent English prose of the twentieth century. He didn't just translate words.
        He built a <em class="text-gold-300 not-italic">system</em>.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-ink-850 rounded-lg border border-ink-700/50 p-6 md:p-8 my-8">
        <p class="text-ink-300 leading-[1.8] mb-6">
          Take the Arabic <span class="font-arabic text-xl text-gold-400 mx-1" dir="rtl">قَلْبًا جَيِّدًا حَسَنًا مُنيرًا</span>.
          Literally: &ldquo;a good, beautiful, luminous heart.&rdquo; Three physical adjectives.
          Shoghi Effendi renders this as <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">&ldquo;a pure, kindly and radiant heart&rdquo;</strong>
          &mdash; three <em class="text-gold-300 not-italic">spiritual</em> qualities. Same structure, entirely different register.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-ink-500 font-mono leading-relaxed">
          His widow R&uacute;h&iacute;yyih Kh&aacute;num explained: he believed &ldquo;Arabic synonyms usually meant the same thing
          but English ones always had a slight shade of difference which made it possible to be more exact
          in rendering the thought.&rdquo;
          <span class="text-ink-600">&mdash; R&uacute;h&iacute;yyih Kh&aacute;num, <em class="not-italic">The Priceless Pearl</em>, p. 202</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p>
        Or consider <span class="font-arabic text-lg text-gold-400 mx-1" dir="rtl">تقلید</span> (<em class="not-italic font-mono text-xs text-ink-400">Taql&iacute;d</em>).
        A dictionary says &ldquo;imitation.&rdquo; But in Islamic jurisprudence
        it carries a deeply negative connotation &mdash;
        the uncritical acceptance of authority without independent investigation.
        So Shoghi Effendi rendered it <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">&ldquo;blind imitation&rdquo;</strong> &mdash;
        adding an adjective that isn't in the Arabic <em class="text-gold-300 not-italic">because the Arabic already implies it</em>
        to any educated reader.
      </p>

      <p>
        He did this across tens of thousands of phrases. The word
        <span class="font-arabic text-lg text-gold-400 mx-1" dir="rtl">مطلع</span> (<em class="not-italic font-mono text-xs text-ink-400">Ma&#7789;li'</em>)
        is consistently rendered with solar imagery &mdash; &ldquo;Dayspring,&rdquo; &ldquo;Day Star,&rdquo;
        &ldquo;Dawning-place&rdquo; &mdash; preserving the cosmological metaphor that pervades
        the original. The root
        <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400 mx-1" dir="rtl">م-ل-ک</span> becomes
        &ldquo;sovereignty,&rdquo; &ldquo;dominion,&rdquo; or &ldquo;kingdom&rdquo;
        depending on context &mdash; sometimes two in the same sentence:
        <span class="text-gold-200">&ldquo;My sovereignty endureth and My dominion perisheth not.&rdquo;</span>
      </p>

      <p class="text-ink-400">
        Franklin Lewis, the University of Chicago Persian scholar, put it beautifully:
        Shoghi Effendi's approach was <em>artistic rather than strictly doctrinal</em>
        &mdash; aimed at recreating &ldquo;the psychological and spiritual experience of
        reading the original.&rdquo; Like a musical conductor, he chose the tempo, the attack,
        the mode of expression &mdash; and
        <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">&ldquo;has not played a single wrong note.&rdquo;</strong>
        <span class="text-ink-600 text-xs font-mono block mt-2">&mdash; Franklin Lewis, &ldquo;Scripture as Literature,&rdquo; <em class="not-italic">Bah&aacute;'&iacute; Studies Review</em> 12 (2004)</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE UNATTAINABLE GOAL ===== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 -mx-6 px-6">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-b from-ink-900 via-ink-950 to-ink-900 -z-10"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_center,_rgba(234,200,114,0.04)_0%,_transparent_70%)] -z-10"></div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-gold-500/60 mb-4">The invitation</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-10">
        He built it to &ldquo;assist others.&rdquo;
      </h2>

      <blockquote class="relative pl-6 border-l border-gold-400/30 mb-4">
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-300 leading-relaxed italic font-light">
          &ldquo;This is one more attempt to introduce to the West, in language however
          inadequate, this book of unsurpassed pre-eminence among the writings of the
          Author of the Bah&aacute;'&iacute; Revelation. The hope is that it may <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal not-italic">assist others</strong>
          in their efforts to approach what must always be regarded as the unattainable
          goal &mdash; a befitting rendering of Bah&aacute;'u'll&aacute;h's matchless utterance.&rdquo;
        </p>
      </blockquote>
      <p class="text-xs text-gold-500/50 font-mono tracking-wide mb-10 pl-6">
        &mdash; Shoghi Effendi, Foreword to the <em class="not-italic text-gold-500/70">Kit&aacute;b-i-&Iacute;q&aacute;n</em>
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-ink-400 leading-[1.8]">
        <p>
          Read that again. Shoghi Effendi didn't frame his translations as the final word.
          He called them <em class="text-ink-300 not-italic">an attempt</em> &mdash; and expressed the hope that
          his work would <em class="text-ink-300 not-italic">assist others</em> in approaching
          the unattainable goal &mdash; a <em class="text-ink-300 not-italic">befitting</em> rendering of Bah&aacute;'u'll&aacute;h's matchless utterance.
          His corpus isn't a locked vault. It's a <em class="text-gold-300 not-italic">model</em> &mdash;
          a vast, internally consistent demonstration of how sacred translation should work.
        </p>
        <p>
          That's why CTAI puts his entire corpus of translations at the center of every deliberation.
          Not to copy his renderings, but to learn <em class="text-ink-300 not-italic">how he chose</em> &mdash;
          and to give future translators the same depth of reference he built over thirty years,
          available in seconds rather than decades.
        </p>
        <p>
          He wrote every sentence aloud. He kept a 1934 Webster's Dictionary at hand.
          He read Gibbon and Carlyle for their prose rhythms.
          He revised the Hidden Words <em class="text-gold-300/80 not-italic">four times</em> &mdash;
          1924, 1925, 1929, and 1954. The result was
          &ldquo;a grand synthesis of English majestic writing &mdash;
          Jacobean, Restoration, Victorian, and Edwardian &mdash;
          blended seamlessly into a new literary creation.&rdquo;
          <span class="text-ink-600 text-xs font-mono">&mdash; Glenford Mitchell, &ldquo;The Literature of Interpretation,&rdquo; <em class="not-italic">World Order</em> 7:2 (1972&ndash;73)</span>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== LIVE EXAMPLE ===== -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-gold-500/60 mb-4">From the corpus</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-3">
        See what that looks like in practice
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm font-mono">2,530 paragraphs, indexed and searchable</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-6">
      <a href="/models/the-hidden-words/2/" class="lg:col-span-3 group block bg-ink-850 rounded-xl border border-ink-700/40 hover:border-gold-500/30 transition-all overflow-hidden">
        <div class="p-8 md:p-10">
          <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-wider text-ink-500 uppercase">The Hidden Words &middot; Arabic &sect;1</span>
            <span class="text-gold-500/0 group-hover:text-gold-500/80 transition-all text-xs font-mono">View &rarr;</span>
          </div>
          <p class="font-arabic text-2xl md:text-3xl leading-loose text-gold-300/80 mb-8 text-right" dir="rtl">
            يَا ابْنَ الرُّوْحِ<br/>
            فِي أَوَّلِ القَوْلِ امْلِكْ قَلْبًا جَيِّدًا حَسَنًا مُنيرًا لِتَمْلِكَ مُلْكًا دائِمًا باقِيًا أَزَلًا قَدِيمًا
          </p>
          <div class="w-12 h-px bg-gold-500/20 mb-6"></div>
          <p class="text-ink-200 leading-relaxed text-lg">
            O SON OF SPIRIT!<br/>
            My first counsel is this: Possess a pure, kindly and radiant heart, that thine may be
            a sovereignty ancient, imperishable and everlasting.
          </p>
        </div>
      </a>

      <div class="lg:col-span-2 bg-ink-850 rounded-xl border border-ink-700/40 p-8">
        <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-wider text-ink-500 uppercase mb-6">What's happening here</p>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-sm text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-1 rounded-full bg-gold-500/40"></span>
            <p>
              <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400" dir="rtl">جَيِّدًا حَسَنًا مُنيرًا</span>
              &rarr; &ldquo;good, beautiful, luminous&rdquo; becomes
              <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">&ldquo;pure, kindly, radiant&rdquo;</strong> &mdash;
              physical adjectives elevated into spiritual qualities.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-1 rounded-full bg-gold-500/40"></span>
            <p>
              <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400" dir="rtl">مُلْكًا</span>
              &rarr; &ldquo;sovereignty&rdquo; here &mdash; but &ldquo;dominion&rdquo;
              or &ldquo;kingdom&rdquo; elsewhere. Context decides.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-1 rounded-full bg-gold-500/40"></span>
            <p>
              <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400" dir="rtl">أَزَلًا قَدِيمًا</span>
              &rarr; two near-synonyms for eternity expanded into three:
              <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">&ldquo;ancient, imperishable and everlasting&rdquo;</strong>.
            </p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-xs text-ink-500 font-mono pt-3 border-t border-ink-700/40">
            Every paragraph gets a deep reference page.
            <a href="/models/" class="text-gold-500 hover:text-gold-400 ml-1 transition-colors">Explore &rarr;</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== DIVIDER ===== -->
  <div class="flex items-center gap-4 my-4">
    <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-ink-700 to-transparent"></div>
    <span class="font-arabic text-gold-500/30 text-2xl select-none" aria-hidden="true">&#1757;</span>
    <div class="flex-1 h-px bg-gradient-to-r from-transparent via-ink-700 to-transparent"></div>
  </div>

  <!-- ===== THE MODERN PROBLEM ===== -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-20">
    <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-ink-500 mb-4">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-6">
      Today we have instant AI translations.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-ink-300 leading-[1.8] mb-6">
      You can paste a Tablet of Bah&aacute;'u'll&aacute;h into any large language model
      and get a translation in seconds. It'll be grammatical. It might even be elegant.
    </p>
    <p class="text-2xl text-gold-200 font-light mb-10">
      But it won't be <em class="italic">this</em>.
    </p>

    <div class="space-y-1 mb-10">
      {[
        {
          num: '01',
          title: 'AI translation averages everything',
          desc: `LLMs have been trained on millions of translations — every quality level,
            every tradition, every amateur effort. When you ask for a translation,
            you get the mean. Shoghi Effendi's distinctive voice? Drowned out by sheer volume.`,
        },
        {
          num: '02',
          title: 'AI translation forgets',
          desc: `Shoghi Effendi's complete translations span thousands of pages.
            No context window can hold them. That means no AI translator
            can know that مطلع appears 23 times in the corpus, always with solar imagery,
            unless someone tells it.`,
        },
        {
          num: '03',
          title: 'AI translation works alone',
          desc: `A single prompt produces a single rendering with a single set of biases.
            When there's a hard call — "sovereignty" or "dominion"? "chosen" or "singled out"? —
            a single model silently picks one and moves on.
            The tension between options, which is often where the insight lives,
            vanishes without a trace.`,
        },
      ].map((item, i) => (
        <div class="group flex gap-6 p-5 rounded-lg hover:bg-ink-850/80 transition-colors">
          <span class="shrink-0 font-mono text-xs text-gold-500/40 pt-1">{item.num}</span>
          <div>
            <p class="text-gold-100 font-medium mb-1.5">{item.title}</p>
            <p class="text-ink-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE WHAT-IF ===== -->
  <section class="relative py-20 -mx-6 px-6">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-ink-850 via-ink-900 to-ink-900 -z-10"></div>
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[radial-gradient(ellipse_at_top_left,_rgba(234,200,114,0.06)_0%,_transparent_50%)] -z-10"></div>

    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-gold-400 mb-4">The shift</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-10">
        But what if it didn't have to?
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-ink-300 leading-[1.8] text-lg font-light">
        <p>
          What if you could give three AI translators distinct specializations &mdash;
          literary, cultural, theological &mdash; and teach them to consult?
          What if you gave them a research assistant with the <em class="text-gold-300 not-italic">entire</em>
          indexed corpus of Shoghi Effendi's translations, searchable
          by keyword and meaning?
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-400">
          What if, before anyone translated a word, that research assistant
          looked up every theologically significant term in your passage
          and assembled a dossier of exactly how Shoghi Effendi handled each one &mdash;
          with full surrounding context?
        </p>
        <p class="text-ink-400">
          What if each translator worked independently &mdash; no peeking &mdash;
          and then they critiqued each other's renderings?
          What if they argued about it, revised, argued again,
          and only settled when they converged or admitted genuine disagreement?
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 p-6 md:p-8 rounded-xl border border-gold-500/20 bg-gold-500/[0.03]">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gold-200 font-light leading-relaxed">
          That's CTAI. A translation committee that never forgets a precedent,
          never tires of deliberation, and shows all its work.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===== THE COMMITTEE ===== -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="text-center mb-14">
      <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.35em] uppercase text-gold-500/60 mb-4">Meet the committee</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-light text-gold-100 tracking-tight mb-3">
        Four Virtual Translators engaged in Virtual Consultation
      </h2>
      <p class="text-ink-500 max-w-xl mx-auto text-sm">
        Each agent brings a different lens to the same text &mdash;
        and they argue about it until they get it right.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Research Agent -->
    <div class="bg-ink-850 rounded-xl border border-ink-700/40 p-8 md:p-10 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-5">
        <div class="shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-ink-800 border border-ink-700/60 flex items-center justify-center text-gold-400 text-sm font-mono">J</div>
        <div class="flex-1">
          <div class="flex items-baseline gap-3 mb-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg text-gold-100">Jafar &mdash; The Research Assistant</h3>
            <span class="font-mono text-[10px] text-ink-500 tracking-wider">RETRIEVAL + ANALYSIS</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-ink-500 text-sm mb-4">Does its homework before anyone translates a word</p>
          <p class="text-ink-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Analyzes every significant term in your source passage,
            searches the full indexed corpus &mdash; keyword <em class="text-gold-300/70 not-italic">and</em> semantic &mdash;
            and assembles a <strong class="text-gold-200 font-normal">Reference Packet</strong>:
            a dossier of every relevant precedent, with full surrounding context.
          </p>
          <div class="bg-ink-900 rounded-lg p-5 text-sm border border-ink-800/80">
            <p class="text-ink-500 mb-4 font-mono text-[10px] tracking-wider uppercase">
              Example report: <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400 text-base normal-case" dir="rtl">إنصاف</span> <span class="text-ink-600">(in&#7779;&aacute;f)</span>
            </p>

            <!-- Term heading -->
            <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2 pb-1 border-b border-ink-800/40 mb-2">
              <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400" dir="rtl">إنصاف</span>
              <span class="text-ink-500 font-mono text-[10px]">in&#7779;&aacute;f</span>
              <span class="text-ink-700 font-mono text-[10px]">ن-ص-ف</span>
              <span class="text-ink-600 text-[10px]">&mdash; equity, fairness</span>
              <span class="ml-auto text-[10px] text-ink-600 font-mono">11 hits</span>
            </div>

            <!-- Rendering 1 -->
            <div class="mb-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
                <span class="font-arabic text-gold-400/60 text-xs" dir="rtl">إنصاف</span>
                <span class="text-ink-600 text-[10px]">&rarr;</span>
                <span class="text-gold-200 text-xs font-medium">&ldquo;equity&rdquo;</span>
                <span class="text-ink-600 text-[10px] font-mono">&times;5</span>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start text-[11px] leading-relaxed ml-4 mb-1">
                <span class="font-arabic text-ink-400 shrink-0" dir="rtl">...بانصاف و عدل نظر نمائيد...</span>
                <span class="text-ink-700 mx-1.5 shrink-0">|</span>
                <span class="text-ink-300">...look with equity and justice...</span>
                <span class="text-ink-600 font-mono text-[9px] ml-2 shrink-0 pt-0.5">KIQ&sect;6</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- See also -->
            <div class="mt-2 pt-2 border-t border-ink-800/30">
              <span class="text-[10px] text-ink-600 font-mono tracking-wider uppercase">See also</span>
              <div class="mt-1.5">
                <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-1">
                  <span class="font-arabic text-amber-400/60 text-xs" dir="rtl">عدل</span>
                  <span class="text-ink-500 font-mono text-[10px]">'adl</span>
                  <span class="text-ink-700 text-[10px]">&mdash; also &rarr;</span>
                  <span class="text-amber-300/70 text-[10px]">&ldquo;justice&rdquo;, &ldquo;equity&rdquo;</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex items-start text-[11px] leading-relaxed ml-4 mb-1">
                  <span class="font-arabic text-ink-400 shrink-0" dir="rtl">...يا قوم العدل أحبّ الأشياء عندی الانصاف...</span>
                  <span class="text-ink-700 mx-1.5 shrink-0">|</span>
                  <span class="text-ink-300">...O PEOPLE OF JUSTICE! The best beloved... is Justice...</span>
